<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 1:44PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Richland and
Ashland Counties through 215 PM EDT...
At 144 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hayesville, or 7 miles east of Mansfield, moving north at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ashland, New London, Hayesville, Savannah, Polk, Sullivan,
Perrysville, Lucas, Jeromesville, Bailey Lakes, Mifflin, Nova, Nankin
and Olivesburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
